pois.name: Lugnaquilla
pois.description: Lugnaquilla, at 925 metres, is the highest Irish mountain outside of Kerry.

pois.name: Carrauntoohil
pois.description: Carrauntoohil is the highest mountain in Ireland at 1,038.6 metres

pois.name: Tonelagee
pois.description: At 817 metres, Tonelagee is the third highest in the Wicklow mountains. It's name means 'backside to the wind'
